This weekend I checked out Northern Michigan’s newest cabin community, @kotiexperience 

KOTI is a series of 14 Scandanavian-style cabins in Williamsburg, Michigan, just outside of iconic Traverse City. This group of cabins is conveniently located within a quarter mile of Grand Traverse Bay. 

It’s just far enough away from the hustle and bustle of the city that you can have a sense of peace and quiet while still being near to activities and nightlife.

One bonus is that the TART runs through the property. This is a paved urban transportation and recreation corridor with an eastern end-point at M-72/Bates Rd in Acme Township and a western end-point at Carter Rd in Traverse City, where it links with the Leelanau Trail.

It’s also near so many great attractions in the area. Here’s what we did 🔽🔽🔽

⭐Played with my niece at the Clinch Park Splash Pad
⭐Ate a phenomenal veggie burger at @oakwoodproperburgers
⭐Checked out @brysestate and their secret flower field
⭐Had a picnic back at the cabin with food from @crocodile_palace

Make sure to follow @kotiexperience and stay up to date as they continue to expand their amazing rental community!

This is my second time staying at Fernside A-frame by @tworiversretreats and it may have been the best visit yet! 🌿🌿

During warmer months you can tube down the Sturgeon River all the way to the State Park. It’s a short walk back to the cabin. It’s one of the coolest things I’ve seen  on all my cabin adventures! 🌊🛶

Here are some ideas of activities to do while you’re in the area 

✨Burt Lake State Park: This park is a public recreation area covering 406 acres on the south shore of Burt Lake. It’s within walking distance of the A-frame
✨Mackinac Island: This slice of paradise is an island that prohibits automobiles. People get around via bikes or horse-drawn carriages. It’s only a half hour drive from the cabin
✨Nature’s Megaphone in Banwell Nature Preserve: A man named Charles Dawley created Nature’s Megaphone with the help of local high school students. It’s inspired by an Estonian art installation of three megaphones. Inside the megaphone, the sounds of the forest are amplified.
✨Harbor Springs: This quaint Michigan town is only about a half-hour drive from the cabin.

Ask and you shall receive! You’ve been requesting more affordable cabin content and this adorable tiny house fits this bill. The tiny house at @mistateparks Waterloo State Recreation area is located on Sugarloaf Lake. It sleeps 4 and has everything you need for an amazing vacation. Some things to consider before you book your trip: 

1. You bring your own linens. I LOVE this. I think it’s so much fun to decorate the space and make it my own. 
2. There is no bathroom in the cabin, but the modern community bathrooms are a short walk and they are really nice. They have showers and lots of mirrors and counter space for getting ready.
3. You can rent kayaks or a row boat for water activities
4. There is a hiking trail in the campground, but the main park has so much more! Don’t be afraid to leave the campground
5. There is a refrigerator and A/C
6. There is a fire pit, picnic table, and charcoal grill

Holly and I had so much fun at this cabin. It feels so much bigger inside than we were expecting. It’s clean, on the water, and inexpensive. I think this checks all the boxes for fun and affordable family vacation. Visit my recent blog post for rental info.

This charming cottage is located on Buhl Lake🌊 and is part of the Lake Arrowhead community. Guests have access to a seasonal community pool, park, and boat launch. 

The midcentury modern interior is beautifully designed and oh-so-cozy. But the best part is spending time in the hot tub with a view that is second to none.

I highly recommend booking this one-of-a-kind rental!

I’ve been getting a lot of requests to showcase affordable cabins.  In response I say @Mistateparks is a great option for those looking to spend less. Over the last three years I’ve stayed in at least one of these cabins a year, sometimes two! These cabins are generally in beautiful locations since they are located right in a State Park. They are usually close to hiking and other outdoor activities. And the best part is that they usually are around $100/night - depending on the cabin. 

Today I’m highlighting one of my all time favorites, Crabapple. It’s such a cute ‘lil a-frame in Pontiac Lake State Rec Area. It sleeps two, is located within a campground, and is a very short walk to the community bathrooms. There is a charcoal grill and fire pit on the property. Jamie and I stayed here in mid September a few years ago and had the time of our lives. We hiked, decorated, had a bonfire, and watched spooky movie’s we’d downloaded on our iPad. 

Learn more about this cabin by following this link: https://moodycabingirl.wordpress.com/2021/09/30/pontiac-lake-state-recreation-area-waterford-twp-michigan/

After staying at @acornfamilyretreats in April, I knew I had to go back and visit it when the weather turned warmer! It was an amazing experience in the Spring, and I knew warmer weather would have its own unique experiences to offer. 

This time around I brought the WHOLE family - my three sisters and parents, my niece, and the family pups Linus and Lucy. We had the most magical stay! We spent our days enjoying the beach, walking on the hiking trail that is a hop, skip, and jump away, and making crafts provided by our hosts! 

Downtown East Tawas is only 10 minutes away and so much fun. We played in parks, ate at a local pizza joint, and checked out the local shops. 

We also hiked Lumbermen’s Monument, a really amazing trail only a half hour away.

Stop scrolling, and check out this incredible lakefront cabin in Marcellus Michigan, @lakehuyckresort 

This magical a-frame sleeps 6, has 3 bedrooms, and 1 bath. Did I mention it’s DOG friendly? 

If you love the a-frame, you’ll be excited to learn there is a sister cabin next door that sleeps 8 and is just as charming. This means this property could be great for family gatherings or friend trips. 

Check out everything we did: 

-Dinner: @therockatbigfishlake - This restaurant is a very short drive from the cabin, and such a cool spot. It’s located near a lake and has a log cabin vibe. The food was awesome. 
-Coffee:  @patchandremington This may just be the coolest coffee shop we’ve ever visited. We walked inside to see beautiful artwork hanging on the walls in the front gallery.  We learned that that the cafe rotates art exhibits from up and coming artists. Then two adorable dogs greeted us with wagging tails. There are computers on site so locals who don’t have access to high speed internet can get online. 
-Wineries: We visited a few and they were all amazing, but Cody Kresta was our favorite. We felt like we were transported into a Gilmore Girls episode mixed with a fairy tale. 
-Hiking: We hiked nearby Fred Russ Forest Park which was spectacular this time of year. Heads up it an get a bit muddy so wear proper shoes!
-Of course we had a ton of fun at the cabin. We kayaked, had a bon fire, played board games, drank wine, and just relaxed. It was so much fun. I highly recommend @lakehuyckresort for your next cabin trip!

Guys, I think I found everyone’s dream Airbnb. @Water_camp ‘s Birch Cottage is a vintage modern cottage right on the shores of Torch Lake. Yes, THE Torch Lake!  Imagine summers spent on the lake - swimming, renting a pontoon, hanging out at the sand bar… it’s a summer playground! For those of you who don’t know, Torch Lake is the longest inland lake in our state and is world famous for it’s clear, Caribbean blue waters. 

I stayed in November -  so not quite swimming weather - but we did get some gorgeous sunsets, and we spent much time at the cabin looking out over the water. 

This Northern Michigan cabin sleeps 6 and has 1 bathroom. It’s near many hiking trails, restaurants, and stores. I brought my 2-year-old niece, and there was plenty for her to do, including a visit to Friske Family Farm where we played on the indoor treehouse and had a lunch of artisanal sandwiches.
